  "body": "Currently, when right-clicking an account from the wallet area, the user sees the options for `Add new account` and `Add watch-only account`. \r\n\r\nThese 2 actions should be removed from the account context menu given:\r\n1) There are not technically contextual to that account\r\n2) The user can access those 2 actions from the `+` icon button at the top of the account list or via the context menu invoked by right-clicking the empty space in the wallet list panel\r\n\r\n<img width=\"799\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-05-15 at 10 40 37\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/2430f330-d4a8-4656-891a-6c7405dde425\">\r\n\r\nThis change mainly impacts the Add/Edit wallet flows in the Wallet v2 file but will be changed in the Desktop Settings file also where relevant.\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/FkFClTCYKf83RJWoifWgoX/Wallet-v2?type=design&node-id=13909-410577&t=phJiBTpvcsgpMZOG-4\r\n\r\ncc @saledjenic (as discussed, thanks!)",
