    "body": "> @benjthayer what happens in case of right click in between account, currently:\r\n> \r\n> ![Image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/491074/242798857-a46ba13c-0469-4fe0-ac8a-d5ae33f46523.png)\r\n\r\nI think we should keep the context menu when right-clicking between accounts - we teach the user that they can click on any empty space in the account list to get the context menu to add a new account so that technically applies if they right-click between accounts. \r\n\r\nI would remove the `Copy address` menu item however - there isn't much reason to keep that item even in the disabled state as the user is not at that point expecting to see any account specific menu items. \r\n\r\ncc. @John-44 ",
